---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="AI Moderation"
  description="How Lythaus uses AI to keep the platform safe and human-first."
  canonicalPath="/ai-moderation"
>
  <section class="section">
    <h1>AI-Powered Moderation</h1>
    <p>
      Lythaus uses a layered moderation pipeline to protect the community while
      keeping humans in the loop.
    </p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Hive AI (primary)</strong> — every post is scored for toxicity,
        spam, and policy violations in real time.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Azure Content Safety (fallback)</strong> — a second layer catches
        anything Hive misses and provides category-level severity scores.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Human review</strong> — flagged content is queued for moderators.
        No post is removed by AI alone.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Transparency</h2>
    <p>
      If your post is flagged, you will see the reason and can appeal. Our
      moderation console gives moderators full context before any action is
      taken.
    </p>

    <h2>Appeals</h2>
    <p>
      Every moderation decision can be appealed. Appeals are reviewed by a
      human moderator — never by the same AI that flagged the content.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="AI & Moderation"
  description="How Lythaus uses AI for content safety and moderation."
  canonicalPath="/ai-moderation"
>
  <section class="section">
    <h1>AI &amp; Moderation</h1>
    <p>
      Lythaus uses AI-assisted screening as part of its content safety pipeline.
      Automated checks run before publication; human moderators review flagged
      content and make final decisions.
    </p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Content is submitted by the author.</li>
      <li>Automated safety screening checks for policy violations.</li>
      <li>Flagged content is routed to human moderators for review.</li>
      <li>Authors can appeal any moderation decision.</li>
      <li>Community members participate in the appeals process.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Transparency</h2>
    <p>
      All moderation actions are logged. Authors receive clear explanations
      for any action taken on their content. The appeals process is
      available for every decision.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
